inspector.description: Top 250 contracts by Chaos Score (Vol × IV).
inspector.sql_logic:
SELECT 
    TRADE_DATE,
    TICKER,
    CONTRACT,
    DTE,
    MONEYNESS,
    VOLUME,
    IV,
    OPTION_TYPE,
    CHAOS_SCORE -- Pre-calculated in dbt (Volume * IV)
FROM STOCKS_ELT_DB.PREP.int_massive__chaos_scatter
WHERE TRADE_DATE >= DATEADD('day', -14, CURRENT_DATE())
ORDER BY TRADE_DATE ASC, CHAOS_SCORE DESC
inspector.dbt_logic:
-- models/intermediate/int_massive__chaos_scatter.sql

{{ config(
    materialized = 'incremental',
    unique_key = 'id',
    cluster_by = ['trade_date', 'ticker'], 
    incremental_strategy = 'merge'
) }}

with source as (
    select * from {{ ref('int_massive__stocks_options_joined') }}
    
    {% if is_incremental() %}
      -- Optimization: Look back 3 days to catch any late-arriving data
      where trade_date >= dateadd(day, -3, (select max(trade_date) from {{ this }}))
    {% endif %}
)

select
    id,
    trade_date,
    underlying_ticker as ticker,
    option_symbol as contract,
    dte,
    moneyness,
    option_volume as volume,
    implied_volatility_calc as iv,
    
    -- Metadata for frontend
    option_type,
    strike_price,
    
    -- Pre-calculate "Chaos Score" for easier debugging/sorting downstream if needed
    (option_volume * implied_volatility_calc) as chaos_score

from source
where 
    -- 1. Ticker Filter: Keep your specific watchlist
    underlying_ticker in ('NVDA', 'TSLA', 'SPY', 'GOOGL', 'AAPL', 'AMZN', 'MSFT')
    
    -- 2. "Casino" Filter: Only short-dated contracts (Gamma exposure)
    and dte <= 45
    
    -- 3. Moneyness Filter: Remove deep OTM/ITM noise (focus on the battleground)
    and moneyness between 0.5 and 1.5
    
    -- 4. Data Quality
    and option_volume > 0
    and iv > 0

-- 5. THE RANKING OPTIMIZATION
-- This limits the storage to ONLY the top 250 rows per ticker/day.
-- The database does the heavy sorting once (at build time), so your API doesn't have to.
QUALIFY ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
    PARTITION BY underlying_ticker, trade_date 
    ORDER BY (option_volume * implied_volatility_calc) DESC
) <= 250
inspector.dbt_yml:
- name: int_massive__chaos_scatter
    description: >
      Feeds the 'Chaos Index' Scatter Plot.
      [PERFORMANCE]: Materialized View that pre-filters the top 250 most volatile contracts.
      Eliminates browser lag by performing ranking at build time.
    tags: ["dashboard", "risk", "scatter", "incremental"]
    columns:
      - name: chaos_score
        description: "Rank Metric: Volume * IV. Determines bubble Z-Index."
      - name: iv
        description: "Implied Volatility. Used for bubble color."
      - name: volume
        description: "Option Volume. Used for bubble size."
